From 2c70945bb79ef14d65cd811fb51c2542c3faaa1e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kien Nguyen <kien.n.quang@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 2026 12:24:08 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Add Windows emacsclient signal support

* lib-src/emacsclient.c (--pid, --signal, get_server_pid):
Add Windows signal option parsing and PID lookup.
(w32_send_signal_or_die): Send signals via named events.
* src/keyboard.c (process_pending_signals): Drain pending
Windows user signals.
(add_user_signal, register_user_signal): Split Windows signal
registration from CRT handler setup.
(process_w32_user_signal_events): Deliver queued Windows user
signals.
* src/keyboard.h (register_user_signal): Declare helper.
(process_w32_user_signal_events): Declare helper.
* src/sysdep.c (init_signals): Register Windows internal user
signals.
* src/w32term.h (w32_get_next_pending_user_signal): Declare
Windows signal queue accessor.
* src/w32xfns.c (init_w32_user_signal_events): Create named
signal events and worker thread.
(delete_w32_user_signal_events): Tear down signal worker state.
(w32_get_next_pending_user_signal): Drain queued signals.
(notify_msg_ready): Wake the main thread on Windows.
(drain_message_queue): Treat WM_EMACS_INPUT_READY as input.
* test/lisp/server-tests.el
(server-tests/emacsclient/signal-by-pid): Add Windows signal
regression test.
